data.description: Situated on a private lakeside in desirable Nix Lakes subdivision, this majestic 4 bedroom, 3.5 bath home exudes charm and comforting appointments to satisfy the most discriminating taste. Up lights nestled into the landscaping at tree bases, branches and home perimeter add dramatic flair and enhance the beautiful architectural features on the home's exterior. Recently completed exterior paint and landscaping invites one into the newly installed flooring on the main level. The kitchen boasts a Gilmore Custom Kitchen with timeless rich cherry cabinetry, granite counter tops, and high end appliances to thrill the consummate chef. Also on the main level, in addition to the dining and main living spaces, is the grand master suite with large on-suite bath with all the features one would expect in a home of this quality. You will be thrilled to find this home has four fireplaces located in the living room, the kitchen/hearth room, the master bedroom and the master bath to add to the warm aesthetic prevalent thru out.  The second floor provides an additional den, three generously sized bedrooms and two full baths. A huge third floor bonus room is completely finished and could just be that perfect hideaway. A large deck overlooks Nix Lake and a second pond making a perfect spot for great outdoor entertaining.  These lakes are owned by an association of adjacent owners with a $400.00 HOA annual assessment. Sellers will consider a flooring allowance with acceptable offer. Call us today for more information about an assumable loan with a low 2.9% interest rate on this home.
